GRAPH <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_BrandNameStylization> {
  <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Digest_BrandNameStylization> a narr:Digest ;
    narr:digestOf <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#BrandNameStylization> ;
    narr:childCount "33"^^xsd:integer ;
    narr:generatedFrom "d1b09a828565de86" ;
    narr:narration """This hub gathers style observations whose dominant note is brand orthography: the [lowercase 'aswritten' with .ai TLD](narr:StyleObs_BrandName) read as a [code-adjacent, anti-corporate identity](narr:Claim_LowercaseBrandStylization), held [lowercase even at sentence start and in repo paths](narr:StyleObs_BrandNameLowercase). That lowercase rule recurs across dozens of children ([1](narr:StyleObs_AswrittenLowercase), [2](narr:StyleObs_aswrittenLowercase), [3](narr:StyleObservation_LowercaseSignal)) and extends to tool names — `compile`, `introspect`, `scope`, `lens` — in the same [code-style casing](narr:StyleObs_BrandNameStylization). The hub also sweeps in non-brand style facts: [staccato verb-only fragments](narr:StyleObs_1), [backtick code spans for tool/workflow names](narr:StyleObs_BacktickToolNames), [systematic bold for taxonomy terms](narr:StyleObs_BoldKeyTerms), all-caps conviction labels like [BOULDER](narr:StyleObs_ConvictionLabel), and a [bolded provisional research-branch flag](narr:StyleObs_AgentSim_ProvisionalFlag). So the region is recognizable as 'how aswritten writes itself' — orthography, formatting, register — not brand strategy.""" ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Claim_LowercaseBrandStylization> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_1> ;
    narr:covers <https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleObs_3> ;
